The paper deals with the use of satellite data and machine learning techniques for predicting urban growth, which falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed End-to-End framework involves the use of cellular automata models, which is a topic of interest in machine learning (cs.LG) and graphics (cs.GR). Additionally, the paper also discusses the challenges of feature selection and the need for a generic approach, which could be relevant to information theory (cs.IT).
